HEADWORD: Iroquois
<hw>Ir`o*quois"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. sing. & pl.</pos>
<ety>[F.]</ety> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A powerful and warlike
confederacy of Indian tribes, formerly inhabiting Central New York and
constituting most of the Five Nations. Also, any Indian of the Iroquois
tribes.</def>⟦br⟧
